Problem 1. The two maximum items in the list:
transactions = [100, 98, 1000, 2500, 299, 1898, 1989, 2001, 50, 10, 70]
max_1 = 2500
max_2 = 2001
trans = [100, 98, 1000, 2500, 299, 1898, 1989, 2001, 50, 10, 70]
max_1 = max_2 = trans[0]

for i in range(0, len(trans)):
    if trans[i] > max_1:
        max_1 = trans[i]
        
for i in range(0, len(trans)):
    if trans[i] > max_2 and trans[i] != max_1:
        max_2 = trans[i]
        
print(max_2, max_1, sep = ', ')


Task 2. Average of the scores in the list:
user_scores = [1, 4, 5, 5, 5, 5, 5, 4, 4, 4, 3, 1]
summ = user_scores[0]

for i in range(1, len(user_scores)):
    summ += user_scores[i]
    
print(summ / len(user_scores))


Problem 3. One of the modifications of linear search:
trans = [-1000, -200, -90, -80, -78, -61, 200, -9, -31, 200, 600, -100, 1000]
summ = 0
for j in range(len(trans)):    
    if trans[j] > 0:        
        summ += trans[j]
print(summ)


Problem 4. Complexity of Binary Search:
list = [15, 20, 30, 34, 45, 56, 67, 78, 90, 100, 110, 120, 135, 140, 150, 165, 166, 168, 192, 195, 200, 222, 226, 300, 350]
key = 140
print("Key:", key)
length = len(list)
a = int(length - 1)
value = list[a]
count = 0

if key < list[0] or key > list[length - 1]:
  value = "No"
  print(False)

if key == list[0] or key == list[length - 1]:
  value = "Yes"
  print(True)

while value != key and value != "No" and value != "Yes":
  c = a
  if key < value:
    length = a
    a = int(a / 2)
    value = list[a]
    count += 1

  if key > value:
    a = int((a + length) / 2)
    value = list[a]
    count += 1
  
  if c == a:
    print(False)
    break

  if value == key:
    print(True)

print("Count:", count)


Task 5. Sorting the top 2 items:
trans = [100, 98, 1000, 2500, 299, 1898, 1989, 2001, 50, 10, 70]
for j in range(len(trans)):
    for i in range(1, len(trans)):
        a = trans[i-1]
        b = trans[i]
        if b < a:
            trans[i] = a
            trans[i-1] = b
print("trans_sort =",trans)

trans = [100, 98, 1000, 2500, 299, 1898, 1989, 2001, 50, 10, 70]
for j in range(2):
    for i in range(1, len(trans)-j):
        if trans[i] < trans[i-1]:
            trans[i-1], trans[i] = trans[i], trans[i-1]
print("trans_sort =",trans)


Task 6. Comparative analysis:
trans = [100, 98, 1000, 2500, 299, 1898, 1989, 2001, 50, 10, 70]
max_1 = max_2 = trans[0]
a = 0

for i in range(0, len(trans)):
    if trans[i] > max_1:
        max_1 = trans[i] 
    a += i
        
for i in range(0, len(trans)):
    if trans[i] > max_2 and trans[i] != max_1:
        max_2 = trans[i]
    a += i
        
print(max_2, max_1, sep = ', ')
print(i)

trans = [100, 98, 1000, 2500, 299, 1898, 1989, 2001, 50, 10, 70]
a = 0
for j in range(2):
    for i in range(1, len(trans)-j):
        if trans[i] < trans[i-1]:
            trans[i-1], trans[i] = trans[i], trans[i-1]
        a += i
print("trans_sort =",trans)
print(i)

The method in problem five is better, since there are one fewer iterations (9 versus 10).


Problem 7. Index of the minimum element in the list:
week = [8, 10, 9, 8, 13, 5, 17]
a = week[0]
for i in range(0, len(week)):
  if week[i] < a:
    a = week[i]
    b = i+1
print("Day(min) =", b)


Task 8. Counting even elements in the list:
week = [8, 10, 9, 8, 13, 5, 17]
for i in range(0, len(week)):
  if week[i] % 2 == 0:
    a = i+1
    print("Day(even) =", a)
    

Problem 9. The longest chain of fives:
scores = [1, 5, 5, 1, 5, 5, 5, 2, 5, 5, 1, 5]
a = b = 0
for i in range(0, len(scores)):
  if scores[i] == 5:
    a += 1
  if scores[i] != 5:
    if b < a:
      b = a
      a = 0
print("5 (Count) =", b)


Task 10. Sort by insertion:
data = [6, 5, 3, 1, 8, 7, 2, 4]
for i in range(1, len(data)):
  a = data[i]
  for j in range(1, i+1):
    if a < data[i-j]:
      data[i-j+1] = data[i-j]
      q = j
  if data[i-q] > a:
    data[i-q] = a
print(data)

